<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./KhymChanur">KhymChanur</a>: (2.2.7, vanilla ToME) If you have no fate, then the oracle will tell you "<em>Well, you have no fate, anyway I'll keep your money!</em>" The last part should probably be something like "<em>but I'll keep your money anways!</em>" <p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: "...keep your money anyway!" 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Changed the text as suggested in 2.3.0 (CVS) 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a class="nonexistent" href="./XandorTikroth">XandorTikroth</a></strong>: That's kinda funny...  Anyway, what about people who do that like Galadriel?  I never thought that she would be such a jerk... perhaps changing the wording a little bit to maybe suggest that she'll accept that money as a donation or something? 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: If there's a reasonably simple way to insert a hook in the code to produce different messages for all the different fate-mongers, that'd be a very nice enhancement. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: More generally, individual speeches for each shop owner would be nice. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: That'd be neat! It'd make the cycling of shopowners more interesting. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./BurbLulls">BurbLulls</a>: That would add a whole new layer of depth to the predujiced races. Shopkeepers <em>really</em> getting snippy about your presence in their shop... 
</p>
